.TH "zynq_gpio_get_direction" 9 "zynq_gpio_get_direction" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zynq_gpio_get_direction \- Read the direction of the specified GPIO pin
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" zynq_gpio_get_direction
.BI "(struct gpio_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pin "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
gpio_chip instance to be worked on
.IP "pin" 12
gpio pin number within the device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function returns the direction of the specified GPIO.
.SH "RETURN"
GPIO_LINE_DIRECTION_OUT or GPIO_LINE_DIRECTION_IN
